{
    "title": "Session Based API",
  "description": "To manage the session lifecycle, I'd use the express-session middleware. It's a key component of this design. It handles the creation and management of sessions and attaches a req.session object to every request. This object holds the session data, making it easy to access user information throughout the application.For a production environment, I'd configure express-session to use a dedicated session store like Connect-Mongo (for MongoDB) or Connect-Redis (for Redis) instead of the default in-memory store. This ensures that session data persists even if the server restarts or if the application scales horizontally across multiple instances."
}

